{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"73c0f6d2-8bf2-4dc","type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"    Now I need to update `production_simulator.go` to implement the snapshot fallback logic. When `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot` fails with \"context location metadata missing\" AND the request has no `SourcePlanID` and no `SnapshotAnchorTime` (full_cluster path), try older snapshots up to 5 minutes.\n\nLet me think about the implementation approach. I need to:\n\n1. In `productionSimulator`, I need access to `GetRecentSnapshotLocations` from the snapshot service. Looking at the current code, `productionSimulator` already has `snapshotService snapshots.Service`.\n\n2. In `RunVariant`, after loading the source plan, we call `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot(snapshotLocation)`. If this fails with a metadata-missing error AND we're on the full_cluster path (`req.SourcePlanID == nil && req.SnapshotAnchorTime == nil`), try fallback.\n\n3. The fallback: call `GetRecentSnapshotLocations(ctx, req.ClusterID, 5*time.Minute)`, iterate from newest to oldest (excluding the first one which we already tried), for each call `GetRebalancerDebugContextLocationForSnapshot` (or better, `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot` since that's what we actually need).\n\nWait, looking at the code more carefully:\n\n```go\nclusterContext, err := s.debugService.LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot(ctx, snapshotLocation)\nif err != nil {\n    return nil, snapshotLocation, fmt.Errorf(\"loading source plan cluster context: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\nSo `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot` wraps `GetRebalancerDebugContextLocationForSnapshot`. If we get an error from `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot`, we need to check if it's a metadata-missing error and then try the fallback.\n\nActually, the simplest approach: when `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot` fails and we're on full_cluster path, get recent snapshots and try each one until one succeeds.\n\nLet me implement this as a method on `productionSimulator`.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"     Now update `production_simulator.go` with the snapshot fallback logic:   "},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.edit:34","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast/services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/production_simulator.go","edits":[{"oldText":"func (s *productionSimulator) RunVariant(ctx context.Context, req mq.AnalysisVariantRequest, mutations []mutation.Mutation) (*executortypes.SimulationResult, string, error) {\n\tctx = metadata.InternalUserContext(ctx, metadata.ValueInternalUserRebalancer)\n\n\tplanID := uuid.New()\n\tsourcePlan, err := s.loadSourcePlan(ctx, req)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, \"\", err\n\t}\n\tsnapshotLocation := sourcePlan.SnapshotLocation\n\n\tclusterContext, err := s.debugService.LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot(ctx, snapshotLocation)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, snapshotLocation, fmt.Errorf(\"loading source plan cluster context: %w\", err)\n\t}","newText":"const snapshotFallbackMaxAge = 5 * time.Minute\n\nfunc (s *productionSimulator) RunVariant(ctx context.Context, req mq.AnalysisVariantRequest, mutations []mutation.Mutation) (*executortypes.SimulationResult, string, error) {\n\tctx = metadata.InternalUserContext(ctx, metadata.ValueInternalUserRebalancer)\n\n\tplanID := uuid.New()\n\tsourcePlan, err := s.loadSourcePlan(ctx, req)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, \"\", err\n\t}\n\tsnapshotLocation := sourcePlan.SnapshotLocation\n\n\tclusterContext, err := s.loadContextWithFallback(ctx, req, snapshotLocation)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, snapshotLocation, fmt.Errorf(\"loading source plan cluster context: %w\", err)\n\t}"},{"oldText":"func (s *productionSimulator) loadSourcePlan(ctx context.Context, req mq.AnalysisVariantRequest) (*rebalancingrepo.Plan, error) {","newText":"func (s *productionSimulator) loadContextWithFallback(ctx context.Context, req mq.AnalysisVariantRequest, snapshotLocation string) (*debug.ClusterContext, error) {\n\tclusterContext, err := s.debugService.LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot(ctx, snapshotLocation)\n\tif err == nil {\n\t\treturn clusterContext, nil\n\t}\n\n\t// Only attempt snapshot fallback for full_cluster trigger type (no source plan, no time anchor).\n\tif req.SourcePlanID != nil || req.SnapshotAnchorTime != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\t// Check if the error is due to missing metadata (the signal to try older snapshots).\n\tif !debug.IsMetadataMissingError(err) {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\trecentLocations, listErr := s.snapshotService.GetRecentSnapshotLocations(ctx, req.ClusterID, snapshotFallbackMaxAge)\n\tif listErr != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, loc := range recentLocations {\n\t\tif loc == snapshotLocation {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tfallbackContext, fallbackErr := s.debugService.LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot(ctx, loc)\n\t\tif fallbackErr == nil {\n\t\t\treturn fallbackContext, nil\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil, err\n}\n\nfunc (s *productionSimulator) loadSourcePlan(ctx context.Context, req mq.AnalysisVariantRequest) (*rebalancingrepo.Plan, error) {"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kimchi-dev","model":"kimi-k2.6","usage":{"input":42358,"output":1200,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43558,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780918409093,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8df73b8039ea8d25"},"timestamp":"2026-06-08T11:35:32.073Z","cwd":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast"}
